Agenda

	* What is encapsulation ?
		Encapsulation is a mechanism of wrapping the data (variables) and code acting on the data
		(methods) together as a single unit.
					or
		Encapsulation describes the ability of an object to hide its data and methods from the rest of the world

	* Implementation of encapsulation ?


	Note : - Accessing variables and methods directly from class is a bad practise.
			 getting or setting a variable or method directly is a bad practise